[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{When SOUTH gives immediate \S support, NORTH's thoughts naturally 
turn to slam. This is a good hand to use Blackwood on, so NORTH bids 4NT.

SOUTH's 5\D answer shows one Ace, which NORTH cleverly deduces 
must be the \CA.

NORTH bids 6\S since SOUTH has not bid strongly enough to think about 7.}

